<div class="res-text richtextContent background-hidden" id="e755f813-9dd7-456c-9ca1-fa4a31b50101" >

    <h2>Dr. Roberto Botelho</h2> 
<p><strong>Organelle Function and Adaptation, Tier II<br> Department of Chemistry and Biology</strong></p> 
<p><a href="https://www.ryerson.ca/cab/facultyandstaff/roberto-botelho/">Roberto Botelho</a> is a cell biologist that investigates the molecular processes responsible for establishing, maintaining and adapting the cell's organelles to stresses like infection. Organelles are very much like the cell's organs, each with their own responsibility. Botelho focuses particularly on lysosomes and phagosomes, organelles responsible for degrading unwanted/damaged material and killing foreign microbes. Some microbes, such as tuberculosis and salmonella, have evolved mechanisms to stop these processes. Thus, Botelho's research aims to better understand these organelles and identify new targets for drug development. <br> </p>
    





